 \|u + w\| = \|u - w\| \iff \langle u, w \rangle + \overline{\langle u, w\rangle} = 0 
\overline{\langle u, w\rangle} = \langle u, w\rangle
F = \mathbb R
\langle u, w\rangle = 0
F = \mathbb C
u = (1, 2)
w = (2i, i)
\|u + w\| = \sqrt{10} = \|u - w\|
\langle u, w \rangle = -4i \ne 0
=||u||^2+0+0+||v||^2, 
\langle u, v \rangle=0
